==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|NL.|en}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|διά||through|tr=dia|lang=grc}} + {{term|ἐγκέφαλος||brain|tr=enkephalos|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˌdaɪənˈsɛfəlɒn/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|diencephalons|diencephala}}

# {{context|neuroanatomy|lang=en}} The region of the human [[brain]], specifically the human [[forebrain]], that includes the [[thalamus]], the [[hypothalamus]], the [[epithalamus]], the [[prethalamus]] or [[subthalamus]], and the [[pretectum]].

